This establishment does not value their customers or their wishes. Customer service goes a long way. If you are someone that require no carbohydrates in their meals for whatever reason(diet, diabetes, etc.), and do not want rice with your meal, you cannot get it that way. You tell them that you will pay the full price, just omit the rice. They refuse to do so saying that they do not sell it like that. Are you kidding me?  The old man at the cash register says "If they want meat only they can buy it and cook it at home". You have got to be kidding? So the customer would have to buy the meals and take their time getting rid of all the rice grains they did not want. I have no idea what kind of customer service they're practicing. If the customer CANNOT rely on this establishment to serve them well, you cannot TRUST that they would serve you food that was not expired or possibly had some outside substance in the food. Spices can hide the smell of bacteria. Why would they care about the quality of food they serve if they do not care to omit something from your meal?
